@startuml
' --- whole-map provenance: cycle that introduced each @id ---
' @cycle(CMP-VIEWER-THEME, 0011)
' @id(CMP-VIEWER-THEME)
' @ref(USE-VIEWER-THEMED)
' @desc(CMP-VIEWER-THEME, "Implemented as crates/mdd-viewer/src/theme.rs, a 2-fn module: register_fonts(ctx: &egui::Context) and apply_theme(ctx: &egui::Context). It owns the bundled font assets under crates/mdd-viewer/assets/fonts/ (Inter-Regular.ttf, Inter-Medium.ttf, JetBrainsMono-Regular.ttf, plus their OFL licences) embedded via include_bytes!, and depends on the egui30-feature build of catppuccin-egui 5.7 and dark-light 2.0. It calls into egui::Context only; ModelRegistry, CycleRegistry, DiagramPage, SvgRasterizer, and DOM-FONT-DATABASE are intentionally not reached.")
' Current-side component view for the Tier-1 theming module. The SVG
' rasterizer (CMP-VIEWER-RENDER-PIPELINE) does not appear here because
' theme.rs never touches it.
title mdd-viewer theming module — ownership (current)

actor "Developer" as Dev

component "MddViewer\n(eframe::App,\ncrates/mdd-viewer/src/lib.rs)" as Viewer
component "theme.rs\nregister_fonts + apply_theme" as Theme
component "assets/fonts/\n(Inter-Regular.ttf,\n Inter-Medium.ttf,\n JetBrainsMono-Regular.ttf,\n include_bytes!)" as Assets
package "External crates" {
  component "catppuccin_egui 5.7\n(feature: egui30)" as Catppuccin
  component "dark_light 2.0" as DarkLight
}
component "egui::Context" as Ctx

Viewer --> Theme : register_fonts(&cc.egui_ctx) once\n+ apply_theme(ctx) each frame
Theme --> Assets : include_bytes!
Theme --> Ctx : ctx.set_fonts(FontDefinitions)
Theme --> DarkLight : detect() each frame
DarkLight --> Theme : Mode::{Light, Dark, Unspecified}
Theme --> Catppuccin : set_theme(ctx, MOCHA | LATTE)
Catppuccin --> Ctx : style.visuals = palette
Theme --> Ctx : style_mut(): spacing + rounding overrides
Ctx --> Dev : themed TopBottomPanel + SidePanels + canvas

note bottom of Theme
  Pure chrome boundary: theme.rs has no
  use mdd_core::… imports, no PathBuf,
  no SVG, no model state. Removing it
  must not change any rendered diagram.
end note

note bottom of Assets
  TTFs and OFL licences ship inside
  the binary. Licences are also recorded
  in this folder's .txt files so that
  redistribution stays compliant.
end note
@enduml
